Interface ModelGenerator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ModelInfo
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ModelGeneratorSymbolic
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultModelGenerator, ModulesFileModelGenerator, ModulesFileModelGeneratorSymbolic, ProductModelGenerator, ProductModelGenerator2, TestModelGenerator

    public interface ModelGenerator
extends ModelInfo
    Interface for classes that generate a probabilistic model: given a particular model state (represented as a State object), they provide information about the outgoing transitions from that state.

      • getTransitionAction

        java.lang.Object getTransitionAction(int i)
                              throws PrismException
        Get the action label of a transition, specified by its index. The label can be any Object, but will often be treated as a string, so it should at least have a meaningful toString() method implemented. Absence of an action label is denoted by null. Note: For most types of models, the action label will be the same for all transitions within the same nondeterministic choice, so it is better to query the action by choice, not transition.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • getTransitionAction

        java.lang.Object getTransitionAction(int i,
                                     int offset)
                              throws PrismException
        Get the action label of a transition within a choice, specified by its index/offset. The label can be any Object, but will often be treated as a string, so it should at least have a meaningful toString() method implemented. Absence of an action label is denoted by null. Note: For most types of models, the action label will be the same for all transitions within the same nondeterministic choice (i.e. for each different value of offset), but for Markov chains this may not necessarily be the case.
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • getChoiceAction

        default java.lang.Object getChoiceAction(int i)
                                  throws PrismException
        Get the action label of a choice, specified by its index. The label can be any Object, but will often be treated as a string, so it should at least have a meaningful toString() method implemented. Absence of an action label is denoted by null. Note: If the model has different actions for different transitions within a choice (as can be the case for Markov chains), this method returns the action for the first transition. So, this method is essentially equivalent to getTransitionAction(i, 0).
        Throws:
        PrismException

      • getStateActionReward

        default double getStateActionReward(int r,
                                    State state,
                                    java.lang.Object action)
                             throws PrismException
        Get the state-action reward of the rth reward structure for state state and action action (r is indexed from 0, not from 1 like at the user (property language) level). If a reward structure has no transition rewards, you can indicate this by implementing the method ModelInfo.rewardStructHasTransitionRewards(int), which may improve efficiency and/or allow use of algorithms/implementations that do not support transition rewards rewards.
        Parameters:
        r - The index of the reward structure to use
        state - The state in which to evaluate the rewards
        action - The outgoing action label
        Throws:
        PrismException
